The Darkflow web client.

Darkflow is Darkwind's official web client. Open play.darkwind.ai in a web
browser and play. There is nothing to install. It is a real terminal with
everything telnet offers, plus optional graphical features driven by the
game.

Panels. Dockable panels show vitals, stats, worth, an XP monitor, your
room, a room image, inventory, group, chat, quests, achievements, buffs,
the sky, fishing, and more. Panels can be docked to either side or floated,
and your layout is remembered between sessions.

Live map. A graphical tile map is built from the exploration of all
players. Clicking a room on the map walks you there step by step, and the
client verifies each step with the game before taking the next.

Area maps. The command areas map followed by an area number opens that
area's map for browsing in its own Area Map pane, separate from the live
map.

Sound. Game-driven sound effects and ambient audio, with volume and mute
controls.

Help. Help topics open in a pop-up window. With screenreader mode on, help
is shown as plain text through the pager instead.

Automation. Aliases, triggers, highlights, and scripts, plus settings
export and import as JSON.

Comfort. Dark and light themes, command history, tab completion, and
screenreader support, including a setting that sends set screenreader on to
the game.

Related help: help monitor, help alias, help scripts, help areas, and help
interface screenreader.
